Package: netlinux-desktop
Version: 1.0-1netlinux1
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: xfce4, xfce4-goodies, lightdm, lightdm-gtk-greeter, xorg, pulseaudio, network-manager, network-manager-gnome, thunar, thunar-archive-plugin, mousepad, ristretto, file-roller, gvfs, gvfs-backends, dbus-x11, fonts-liberation, fonts-dejavu, plymouth, plymouth-themes, openbox, konqueror, xterm, gimp, blender, claude-code, applesmc-next-dkms, battery-tray, chromium-browser-stable, tightvnc, kio-rsync, simplescreenrecorder, qpwgraph, curaengine, rsync, pavucontrol, openssh-server, bridge-utils, net-tools, sudo, curl, wget, git, htop, vim, bash-completion, build-essential, dkms, firmware-linux, nodejs
Maintainer: NetLinux <packages@netlinux.co.uk>
Description: NetLinux Desktop meta-package
 Installs the complete NetLinux desktop stack: Xfce desktop environment,
 Chromium and Firefox browsers, GIMP, Blender, TightVNC, Claude Code,
 and essential system and development tools.
 .
 This is a meta-package that pulls in all dependencies for a
 NetLinux Desktop installation.
